BÅ‚Ä…d testowy

set.seed(1)
n <- nrow(ds)
train <- sample(n, n / 2)
test <- -train
diagnosis_tree2 <- tree(diagnosis ~ . - id - diagnosis, data = ds, subset = train)
tree_class <- predict(diagnosis_tree2, newdata = ds[test,], type = "class")
table(tree_class, ds$diagnosis[test])
##           
## tree_class   B   M
